Correlation and Covariance:
a) Develop a program to find the correlation matrix on iris data.
Code:

  data(iris)
  iris_numeric <- iris[, 1:4]
  cor_matrix <- cor(iris_numeric)
  print(cor_matrix)

b) Plot the correlation plot on dataset and visualize giving an overview of relationships among data on iris data

Code:

    install.packages("corrplot")
    library(corrplot)
    cor_matrix <- cor(iris[, 1:4])
    corrplot(cor_matrix, method="circle", type="upper", tl.col="black", tl.srt=45, 
             addCoef.col="blue", title="Correlation Plot for Iris Dataset")
    
        title = "Correlation Plot for Iris Dataset"
    )

c)Plot the correlation plot on dataset and visualize giving an overview of relationships among data on iris data

Code:

    install.packages("corrplot")
    library(corrplot)
    cor_matrix <- cor(iris[, 1:4])
    corrplot(cor_matrix, method="circle", type="upper", tl.col="black", tl.srt=45, 
             addCoef.col="blue", title="Correlation Plot for Iris Dataset")
    
        title = "Correlation Plot for Iris Dataset"
    )

